[SN]TITLE[SN]
CCTV released in Edinburgh public indecency investigation

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
CCTV footage has been released by police in Edinburgh of a man they wish to trace in connection with a public indecency investigation.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened at about 13:10 on Thursday 28 May in George Street, opposite the Starbucks coffee shop.
Officers are keen to speak to the man or anyone who can help establish his identity.
He is white, in his 40s, between 5ft 10ins and 6ft, of medium build and has short brown hair.
He has a clean-shaven complexion and a red face.
He was wearing a light jacket, black jumper, green t-shirt, brown trousers, black Adidas Samba trainers, sunglasses on his head and was carrying a large black rucksack.
Det Con Sam Johnson, of Police Scotland, said: "This incident happened in a busy city centre location and at least one member of the public witnessed it.
"We are keen to trace the male in the footage as part of our investigation and would ask anyone who recognises him to contact police immediately."
